cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper studies the impact of base station idle mode capability on the network performance of multi-tier and dense heterogeneous cellular networks. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper derives analytical expressions for the coverage probability and the area spectral efficiency in each tier. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper analyzes the impact of the IMC on the performance of all BS tiers. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve multimedia applications in the context of cellular networks. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also less likely but possible as the paper may touch upon security issues related to the idle mode capability of base stations.
